The United States has welcomed the passage of the UN Human Rights Council resolution on "promoting reconciliation, accountability, and human rights in Sri Lanka." The resolution calls on the Government of Sri Lanka to take action to ensure justice, accountability, and reconciliation for all Sri Lankans. The resolution also requests the Office of the High Commissioner to investigate alleged human rights violations and monitor the human rights situation in Sri Lanka. The vote sends a message of concern about the current human rights situation in Sri Lanka and emphasizes the importance of respecting fundamental freedoms. It also shows the commitment of the international community to work with the Government of Sri Lanka for peace, stability, and prosperity for all the people of Sri Lanka.